Angular

ng serve -- open (Auto opens after serve)


app.component.ts— the component class code, written in TypeScript.
app.component.html— the component template, written in HTML.
app.component.css— the component's private CSS styles.


Whenever you want to create a new page type in terminal "ng generate component <page name>"

    The CLI command creates a new folder, src/app/<page name>/

You used *ngFor to display a list.
You used *ngIf to conditionally include or exclude a block of HTML.

Add routes in routing module

Add anchor to values to make them clickable

go to newly created component add activated route and services

CSS

Style specific parts like

h1 {
  color: #369;
  font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  font-size: 250%;
}



Universal

{
  font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
}